  "body": "Hi all,\r\n\r\nAs part of #1307, we need a strategy to handle chain reorgs so that means we need to be able to roll-back the state to a historical state. It is inefficient to store all historical states as at worst, a single state object can weight around 800 Mb. We should instead follow the approach projects such as Geth do with journaling and keeping track of certain pieces of information of previous states for critical scenarios such as reorgs.\r\n\r\nOpening this issue thread for further discussion and planning.",
